## Risks and Mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|------------|
| `Schema.decodeSync(ContractAddress)` throws on non-hex strings | Low | `hash.calculateContractAddressFromHash` always returns hex — but wrap in try/catch in implementation if needed |
| `RpcError` import from starknet.js may not be a class (just a type) | Low | Context confirms it's an exported class with `new` constructor — verified in `node_modules/starknet/dist/index.d.ts:4721` |
| Balance gate in `deployAccount` adds an extra RPC call (latency) | Medium | Acceptable for correctness — deploy is already a multi-RPC operation. Gate prevents wasted gas on unfunded accounts |
| Changing `computeDeployAddress` return type breaks downstream components | Medium | Update all test mocks in this PR. Components consuming the service (AccountDeployFlow) will need updating in their own ticket |
| starknet.js v9 `Account` constructor API shape | Low | Already verified in context: `new Account({ provider, address, signer })` — matches starknet.js v9 |
| Tests that use `as ContractAddress` / `as TxHash` in test fixtures | Medium | Replace with `Schema.decodeSync(ContractAddress)(...)` in test fixtures |

